# Database Rules (PostgreSQL + PostGIS)

## Purpose
Source of truth for all data.

## Structure
- schema/ → table definitions
- migrations/ → versioned changes
- seeds/ → initial data
- functions/ → DB logic
- views/ → reusable queries
- indexes/ → performance
- import/ → OSM pipeline

## Rules
- Always use migrations for changes
- Do NOT manually edit DB without SQL file
- Keep SQL clean and readable

## Geospatial
- Use PostGIS functions:
  - ST_DWithin
  - ST_Intersects
  - ST_Contains

## Performance
- Use GIST indexes for geometry
- Avoid full table scans

## Forbidden
- Do NOT store tiles in database
- Do NOT mix application logic

## Goal
- Clean, versioned, reproducible database